{"title_page": "1999\u20132000 OHL season", "text_new": "The '''1999\u20132000 OHL season''' was the 20th season of the [[Ontario Hockey League]]. The season was the first to award a point for an overtime loss. Twenty teams each played 68 games. The [[Barrie Colts]] won the [[J. Ross Robertson Cup]], defeating the [[Plymouth Whalers]].\n\n==Regular Season==\n===Final standings===\n''Note: DIV = Division; GP = Games played; W = Wins; L = Losses; T = Ties; OTL = Overtime Losses; GF = Goals For; GA = Goals Against; PTS = Points; x = clinched playoff berth; y = clinched division title; z = clinched conference title''\n\n=== Eastern conference ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! | Rank\n! width=\"27.5%\"| Team\n! |DIV\n! width=\"6.5%\"| GP\n! width=\"6.5%\"| W\n! width=\"6.5%\"| L\n! | T\n! | OTL\n! | PTS\n! width=\"6.5%\"| GF\n! width=\"6.5%\"| GA\n|-\n| 1 || align=left| z-[[Barrie Colts]] || align=left| Central || 68 || 43 || 18 || 6 || 1 || '''93''' || 306 || 212\n|-\n| 2 || align=left| y-[[Ottawa 67's]] || align=left| East || 68 || 43 || 20 || 4 || 1 || '''91''' || 269 || 189\n|-\n| 3 || align=left| x-[[Belleville Bulls]] || align=left| East || 68 || 44 || 22 || 2 || 0 || '''90''' || 319 || 227\n|-\n| 4 || align=left| x-[[Sudbury Wolves]] || align=left| Central || 68 || 39 || 23 || 5 || 1 || '''84''' || 262 || 221\n|-\n| 5 || align=left| x-[[Kingston Frontenacs]] || align=left| East || 68 || 38 || 22 || 5 || 3 || '''84''' || 258 || 245\n|-\n| 6 || align=left| x-[[Peterborough Petes]] || align=left| East || 68 || 34 || 26 || 7 || 1 || '''76''' || 242 || 219\n|-\n| 7 || align=left| x-[[Oshawa Generals]] || align=left| East || 68 || 32 || 30 || 4 || 2 || '''70''' || 227 || 224\n|-\n| 8 || align=left| x-[[North Bay Centennials]] || align=left| Central || 68 || 24 || 35 || 6 || 3 || '''57''' || 214 || 253\n|- style=\"background-color:#cccccc;\"\n| || || || || || || || || || ||\n|-\n| 9 || align=left| [[Toronto St. Michael's Majors]] || 